OL,3,C'It's bonkers': British Gas tells
OL,4,Ccustomer he's #196,000 in credit
OL,6,FThe figure caused astonishment and
OL,7,Fconfusion, especially as British Gas
OL,8,Fwas simultaneously demanding more than
OL,9,F#2,000 from the same customer.
OL,11,FAfter Rod Peach was sent what he calls
OL,12,Fa "bonkers bill" he called the energy
OL,13,Ffirm saying "can you do me a favour,
OL,14,Fcan you take the #2,500 I'm in debt to
OL,15,Fyourselves off the #196,000 and send
OL,16,Fme a check for the rest?"
